# Browserslist configuration for SeventySix

# Targeting ONLY evergreen browsers (auto-updating browsers)

# This eliminates unnecessary polyfills and reduces bundle size

# STRICT: Only the last 2 versions of evergreen browsers

# Desktop Browsers (Auto-updating)

last 2 Chrome versions # Chrome 141-142 (also covers Brave, Arc, Vivaldi)
last 2 Firefox versions # Firefox 143-144
last 2 Safari versions # Safari 26.0-26.1
last 2 Edge versions # Edge 141-142 (Chromium-based)

# Mobile Browsers (Auto-updating)

last 2 ChromeAndroid versions # Chrome Android 142
last 2 FirefoxAndroid versions # Firefox Android 144
last 2 iOS versions # iOS Safari 18.5-18.6, 26.0

# Explicitly EXCLUDE non-evergreen browsers

not dead
not IE 11
not op_mini all

# Result: 12 browser versions (down from 400+)

# - Desktop: Chrome 141-142, Firefox 143-144, Safari 26.0-26.1, Edge 141-142

# - Mobile: Chrome Android 142, Firefox Android 144, iOS Safari 18.5-26.0

#

# This configuration requires browsers with native support for:

# - ES2022 features (async/await, classes, modules, optional chaining, etc.)

# - ES Modules & Dynamic Imports

# - Modern CSS (Grid, Flexbox, Custom Properties, Container Queries)

# - Web Components

# - Service Workers (PWA)

#

# Expected benefits:

# - No polyfills needed (Angular 20 zoneless + ES2022 target)

# - Smaller bundle size (~20-30% reduction)

# - Faster loading and execution

# - Modern browser features available
